      "For someone that likes to collect rainbows of specific cards, I find it very difficult to find a list that shows every possible variation of a card. Topps's [official checklists](https://www.topps.com/media/pdf/2022ToppsSeries1BaseballChecklist.pdf) mention the prominent parallels, but is frequently missing some of the rarer types, like Montgomery Club, team sets, and retail exclusives. I subscribe to [Beckett](https://beckett-www.s3.amazonaws.com/news/news-content/uploads/2022/02/2022-Topps-Series-1-Baseball-Checklist.xlsx), but they are frequently missing some of variations. As a software developer, I honestly don't have any idea what this team is thinking most of the time. Entire obvious parallels or cards will frequently not be listed. And it costs $16 a month, which is ridiculous. Cardboard Connection has great [Excel-based checklists](https://www.cardboardconnection.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/2022-Topps-Series-1-Baseball-checklist-Excel-spreadsheet.xlsx), but again, doesn't have any information about all of the possible parallels. Checklist Center and BreakNinja have [some](https://www.checklistcenter.com/2022-topps-series-1-baseball-card-checklist/) decent [data](https://www.breakninja.com/baseball/2022-Topps-Series-1-Baseball-Checklist.php), but still miss a few details, and have nothing to download. If there's a secret place you're finding this stuff, I'd love for you to share it. Otherwise, I'm thinking about building it.",
